content:
Assign a product to as many as five categories in your store and preview the results without leaving the add product page. The new product’s details are saved to your store’s default buyer group, entitlement policy, CMS workspace, price book, strikethrough price book, and catalog. Previously, you added this information manually.

Where: This change applies to B2B and D2C Commerce in Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

How: To turn live preview on or off, click the preview icon (1).
title: Previewing Products in Salesforce
